26:41.060 --> 26:44.820
The incident was reported in the local paper, and seeing

26:44.820 --> 26:47.720
a national press was buzzing with news of what came

26:47.720 --> 26:50.080
to be called the Loch Ness Monster.

26:51.860 --> 26:55.640
But legendings of large water creatures in Loch Ness go

26:55.640 --> 26:57.060
back much further than 1933.

26:58.500 --> 27:02.620
In the 6th century A.D., the Irish missionary St.

27:02.800 --> 27:05.880
Columba, was said to have banished a monster which attacked

27:05.880 --> 27:06.700
